      "date": "2012-08-03 16:25:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe commit message doesn't explain why there is a problem and how this fixed the problem.  \n\nRemoving the bind mount will break testing when running from the build tree.\n\nOne option that I've proposed in the past is to call mount.lustre directly, instead of using \"mount -t lustre\" call it. That would allow finding mount.lustre in the PATH. However, it may also need some fixes to mount.lustre to handle mount options (e.g. setup loop devices, or that could be handled by the test framework itself).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0447781e9858eb71911e48116175e80a296bdd39",
      "author": {
